‘Begin Again’ Calls on James Baldwin to Make Sense of Today

FAN - Family Action Network
July 20 at 4:32 PM ·

post_text: ETHS is collaborating with researchers at Stanford University and University of Denver about the current experiences of high school students during the COVID-19 pandemic. We are interested in learning more about how the pandemic has impacted students’ emotional well-being, social relationships, physical health, and academic motivation.

post_text: Grant awarded to support new research in Evanston schools.
shared_text:
Northwestern University School of Education and Social Policy
April 29 at 5:57 PM ·

The Northwestern-Evanston Education Research Alliance (NEERA) received a $650,000 award to support new research projects related to racial and economic equality and expand the collaborative work between Northwestern University and Evanston schools.The grant was awarded to SESP Dean David Figlio; Eric Witherspoon, superintendent of Evanston Township High School (ETHS) District 202; and Devon Horton, incoming superintendent of Evanston/Skokie School District 65. The project will support new projects by SESP faculty members Megan Bang, Mesmin Destin, and Simone Ispa-Landa, among others. http://spr.ly/61851fiyH

post_text: Wildkit sophomores, interested in college? Check out Evanston Scholars. It has extended its deadline to May 1 to apply for its College Access program. Learn more: ow.ly/6AMn50zkNdw
shared_text:
Evanston Scholars
April 1 at 11:52 AM ·

DEADLINE FOR APPLICATIONS FOR OUR CLASS OF 2022 EXTENDED -- April 13 (Priority Deadline) and May 1 (New Final Deadline)

Due to Covid-19, we are extending the final deadline for applications for the Class of 2022 - current Evanston Township High School (ETHS) sophomores - until May 1.

We are looking for ambitious ETHS sophomores with a minimum 2.7 GPA who would like support with the college access and success process. We primarily work with students who are traditionally first-generation college entrants, low-income students, and students of color. Evanston Scholars offers programming, workshops, and cohort-building experiences that help students get TO and THROUGH college.

TO APPLY:
https://www.evanstonscholars.org/applications.html
